# Docs and plan rules

- Keep docs concise, structured, and decision-oriented.
- Prefer one focused document per topic rather than repeating the same rule across many files.
- When implementation changes product behavior, update the authoritative doc instead of adding a conflicting note elsewhere.
- Plans should describe the next executable slice, its files, risks, and validation steps.
- Commands should be reusable workflow prompts, not one-off notes.
